<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="396" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,602,771]" pageId="5" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,285,602,627]" pageId="5" pageNumber="396">Taxonomy:</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[300,402,603,627]" pageId="5" pageNumber="396">Syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[454,709,602,627]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Xyleborus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calamoides">
<emphasis box="[454,709,602,627]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="396">Xyleborus calamoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NMNH) were examined by SMS. The specimens have an obliquely truncate declivity which is generally associated with 
<emphasis box="[856,932,639,662]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="396">Amasa</emphasis>
. However, multiple Asian xyleborine genera have at least one species with a truncate declivity. The species is transferred to 
<taxonomicName authority="Wood, 1980" authorityName="Wood" authorityYear="1980" box="[1037,1310,674,699]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Microperus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1037,1167,676,699]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="396">Microperus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wood, S. L." box="[1173,1310,674,699]" pageId="5" pageNumber="396" pagination="89 - 97" refId="ref9753" refString="Wood, S. L. (1980) New genera and new synonymy in Scolytidae (Coleoptera). The Great Basin Naturalist, 40, 89 - 97. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 20006" type="journal article" year="1980">Wood, 1980</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
because of the following characters: pronotum type 2 (viewed dorsally), antennal club type 3, scutellum not visible and lack of mycangial tufts.
</paragraph>
